news.title: Illegal sand mining in Bokaro continues despite NGT ban
news.para: Despite an NGT ban, illegal sand mining persists in Bokaro, particularly at Bhathua Ghat, with minimal enforcement. While the mining department reports seizures and fines, the focus on sand mining remains limited, even as illegal extraction continues unabated.

news.title: Shakti Pumps raises ₹292 crore via QIP
news.para: Shakti Pumps has successfully raised Rs 292.60 crore through Qualified Institutional Placement, issuing 31.87 lakh shares at Rs 918 each. The funds will be used to establish a 2.20 GW solar cell and module manufacturing plant in Madhya Pradesh.

news.title: Lodha Developers raises ₹300 crore via NCDs
news.para: Lodha Developers has successfully secured ₹300 crore through the issuance of 30,000 senior, secured, redeemable, listed non-convertible debentures (NCDs). These debentures, each with a face value of ₹1 lakh, offer an interest rate of 7.96% per annum, payable quarterly.

news.title: About ₹30,885 crore worth of land transacted across India in H1 2025
news.para: India's land market boomed in the first half of 2025. Land transactions surpassed the entire previous year. Deals totaled ₹30,885 crore, potentially generating ₹1.47 lakh crore. Mumbai Metropolitan Region led the activity. Tier 2 and 3 cities are emerging as key players. Residential projects are driving the land demand. Joint development agreements are also on the rise.

news.title: KVN Properties & Assetz Group to develop one million sq ft residential project in Bengaluru
news.para: KVN Properties LLP and Assetz Group have partnered in a strategic development management agreement to develop a residential project in North Bengaluru. This collaboration involves nearly one million sq ft of development, valued at ₹1,000 crore.

news.title: Omaxe to invest ₹1,200 crore to develop 450-acre township in Indore
news.para: Omaxe, via its subsidiaries, is set to expand its footprint in Madhya Pradesh by acquiring a 450-acre land parcel along Indore's Super Corridor. The company plans to develop an integrated township with an investment of ₹1,200 crore, expecting to generate ₹2,500 crore in revenue over three years.

news.title: Davanagere leads in distribution of digitised land records in Karnataka
news.para: Davanagere leads Karnataka's Bhoosuraksha initiative, distributing 13,040 digital land record pages, surpassing Belagavi and Koppal. The revenue department has processed 1.1 crore historical land documents since February 2024, with Davanagere digitizing 52.8 lakh pages alone. Citizens can access these records online for a nominal fee, eliminating physical visits.

news.title: Sobha posts pre-sales of ₹2,078 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Sobha achieved record-breaking real estate sales in Q1 FY26, reaching ₹2,078 crore, driven by strong demand in key markets. Bengaluru and Gurugram led sales, while the successful launch of Sobha Aurum in Greater Noida marked the company's entry into the city. The company delivered 594 residential units and launched two new projects, expanding its footprint across 13 cities.

news.title: Telangana HC to hear PIL over 27 acres; worth ₹2,000 crore, now with builders
news.para: The Telangana High Court is hearing a PIL filed by Congress MLAs alleging the illegal transfer of 27 acres of government land in Khajaguda to private developers. The land, valued at over ₹2,000 crore, is reportedly being developed into a high-rise project. The court has asked private respondents to file counters, with the case listed for hearing in two weeks.

news.title: Will appoint administrators if RWAs in Gurugram build illegal structures: DTCP
news.para: Gurugram's Department of Town and Country Planning (DTCP) demolished an illegal religious structure built by the former RWA of Suncity Avenue in Sector 102, following resident complaints. Officials noted a rising trend of RWAs undertaking unauthorized constructions in common areas, violating regulations.

news.title: Thane civic body orders survey of unauthorised constructions in Yeoor area adjoining SGNP
news.para: Thane Municipal Corporation has ordered a survey of illegal constructions in Yeoor. This follows concerns about commercial activities impacting the environment. The survey will identify unauthorized structures. Notices will be issued, followed by enforcement. A coordination committee will be formed. It includes officials from various departments and NGOs.

news.title: Gurugram civic body launches chatbot to provide property tax-related information
news.para: Gurugram residents can now access property tax details via a new chatbot service. The Municipal Corporation of Gurugram (MCG) introduced this service to share tax amounts and payment methods. Residents will receive information through phone calls and texts. This initiative aims to increase transparency and combat fraudulent payment demands.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects ₹100 crore in property tax in April-June
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) collected Rs 100 crore in property tax during the first quarter of the 2025-26 financial year, slightly less than the previous year's Rs 106 crore. This collection was supported by rebates offered for prompt payments, ranging from 6-8%.

news.title: Delhi CM urges Uttar Pradesh CM to help curb illegal sand mining in Yamuna river near border
news.para: Chief Minister Rekha Gupta has appealed to Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath to urgently address illegal sand mining in the Yamuna River along the Delhi-UP border. Gupta highlighted the ecological damage, increased flood risk due to weakened embankments, and concerns raised by the National Green Tribunal.

news.title: NHB asks housing finance companies to pay interest on advance EMIs
news.para: The National Housing Bank (NHB) has mandated that housing finance companies (HFCs) must pay interest to borrowers on advance EMI payments held in sundry accounts, aligning with fair lending practices. NHB is also urging HFCs to prioritize borrower quality over advance collections to mitigate default risks.

news.title: No more building plan approvals needed for small plots in Prayagraj
news.para: Prayagraj residents can rejoice as the Uttar Pradesh Cabinet approves the Building Construction and Development Byelaws 2025. This allows construction on plots up to 100 sqm without prior plan approval, benefiting middle-class families by reducing costs and streamlining the building process.

news.title: Delhi: DUSIB to clear its land of encroachments, provide housing to slum dwellers
news.para: Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (DUSIB) is surveying its land to identify encroachments, mapping jhuggi jhopri clusters, and assessing land parcels for housing development. This initiative supports the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana, aiming to provide pucca housing to eligible slum dwellers.

news.title: Maharashtra: ‘One state one registration’ scheme faces delay over technical & legal concerns
news.para: The "one state one registration" scheme in Pune faces delays due to legal, technical, and administrative challenges, including fraud concerns and stamp duty evasion. While the initiative aims to streamline property registration, issues like impersonation and fraudulent land transfers have emerged as major roadblocks.
